(6, 'Pagination Class', 'assets/images/module/module_default/default.png', 'CodeIgniter\\''s Pagination class is very easy to use, and it is 100% customizable, either dynamically or via stored preferences.\r\n\r\nIf you are not familiar with the term \\"pagination\\", it refers to links that allows you to navigate from page to page, like this:', '<div>\r\n<h2 style=\\"border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(153, 153, 153); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; margin: 28px 0px 16px; padding: 5px 0px 6px; font-family: \\''Lucida Grande\\'', Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: normal;\\">Example</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"margin: 12px 20px 12px 0px; font-family: \\''Lucida Grande\\'', Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\\">Here is a simple example showing how to create pagination in one of your&nbsp;<a href=\\"http://ellislab.com/codeigniter/user-guide/general/controllers.html\\" style=\\"color: rgb(1, 52, 197); background-color: transparent; text-decoration: none; outline-style: none;\\">controller</a>&nbsp;functions:</p>\r\n<code style=\\"font-family: Monaco, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; background-color: rgb(249, 249, 249); border: 1px solid rgb(208, 208, 208); color: rgb(0, 33, 102); display: block; margin: 14px 0px; padding: 12px 10px; line-height: normal;\\">$this-&gt;load-&gt;library(&#39;pagination&#39;);<br />\r\n<br />\r\n$config[&#39;base_url&#39;] = &#39;http://example.com/index.php/test/page/&#39;;<br />\r\n$config[&#39;total_rows&#39;] = 200;<br />\r\n$config[&#39;per_page&#39;] = 20;&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n$this-&gt;pagination-&gt;initialize($config);&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\necho $this-&gt;pagination-&gt;create_links();</code>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\\"font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; margin: 16px 0px 15px; padding: 0px; font-family: \\''Lucida Grande\\'', Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: normal;\\">Notes:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"margin: 12px 20px 12px 0px; font-family: \\''Lucida Grande\\'', Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\\">The&nbsp;<var style=\\"color: rgb(143, 91, 0); font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;\\">$config</var>&nbsp;array contains your configuration variables. It is passed to the&nbsp;<dfn style=\\"color: rgb(0, 98, 12); font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;\\">$this-&gt;pagination-&gt;initialize</dfn>&nbsp;function as shown above. Although there are some twenty items you can configure, at minimum you need the three shown. Here is a description of what those items represent:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\\"list-style-image: url(http://ellislab.com/_user_guide_src_ci/images/arrow.gif); margin: 10px 0px 12px; font-family: \\''Lucida Grande\\'', Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\\">\r\n	<li style=\\"margin-bottom: 9px;\\"><strong>base_url</strong>&nbsp;This is the full URL to the controller class/function containing your pagination. In the example above, it is pointing to a controller called &quot;Test&quot; and a function called &quot;page&quot;. Keep in mind that you can&nbsp;<a href=\\"http://ellislab.com/codeigniter/user-guide/general/routing.html\\" style=\\"color: rgb(1, 52, 197); background-color: transparent; text-decoration: none; outline-style: none;\\">re-route your URI</a>&nbsp;if you need a different structure.</li>\r\n	<li style=\\"margin-bottom: 9px;\\"><strong>total_rows</strong>&nbsp;This number represents the total rows in the result set you are creating pagination for. Typically this number will be the total rows that your database query returned.</li>\r\n	<li style=\\"margin-bottom: 9px;\\"><strong>per_page</strong>&nbsp;The number of items you intend to show per page. In the above example, you would be showing 20 items per page.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"margin: 12px 20px 12px 0px; font-family: \\''Lucida Grande\\'', Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\\">The&nbsp;<var style=\\"color: rgb(143, 91, 0); font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;\\">create_links()</var>&nbsp;function returns an empty string when there is no pagination to show.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\\"font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; margin: 16px 0px 15px; padding: 0px; font-family: \\''Lucida Grande\\'', Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: normal;\\">Setting preferences in a config file</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"margin: 12px 20px 12px 0px; font-family: \\''Lucida Grande\\'', Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\\">If you prefer not to set preferences using the above method, you can instead put them into a config file. Simply create a new file called&nbsp;<var style=\\"color: rgb(143, 91, 0); font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;\\">pagination.php</var>, add the<var style=\\"color: rgb(143, 91, 0); font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;\\">$config</var>&nbsp;array in that file. Then save the file in:&nbsp;<var style=\\"color: rgb(143, 91, 0); font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;\\">config/pagination.php</var>&nbsp;and it will be used automatically. You will NOT need to use the&nbsp;<dfn style=\\"color: rgb(0, 98, 12); font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;\\">$this-&gt;pagination-&gt;initialize</dfn>&nbsp;function if you save your preferences in a config file.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\\"border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(153, 153, 153); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; margin: 28px 0px 16px; padding: 5px 0px 6px; font-family: \\''Lucida Grande\\'', Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; line-height: normal;\\">Customizing the Pagination</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n'),
(12, 'CSS 3 Introduction', 'assets/images/module/module_default/default.png', 'CSS3 is the latest standard for CSS.\r\n\r\nCSS3 is completely backwards-compatible with earlier versions of CSS.\r\n\r\nThis section teaches you about the new features in CSS3!', '<div>\r\n<h2 style=\\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 22px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal;\\">CSS3 Modules</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\\">CSS3 has been split into &quot;modules&quot;. It contains the &quot;old CSS specification&quot; (which has been split into smaller pieces). In addition, new modules are added.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\\">Some of the most important CSS3 modules are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\\">\r\n	<li>Selectors</li>\r\n	<li>Box Model</li>\r\n	<li>Backgrounds and Borders</li>\r\n	<li>Image Values and Replaced Content</li>\r\n	<li>Text Effects</li>\r\n	<li>2D/3D Transformations</li>\r\n	<li>Animations</li>\r\n	<li>Multiple Column Layout</li>\r\n	<li>User Interface</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr style=\\"background-color: rgb(212, 212, 212); color: rgb(212, 212, 212); height: 1px; border-top-width: 0px; clear: both; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal;\\" />\r\n<h2 style=\\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 22px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal;\\">CSS3 Recommendation</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\\">The CSS3 specification is still under development by W3C.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\\">However, many of the new CSS3 properties have been implemented in modern browsers.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n'),
(13, 'CSS3 Borders', 'assets/images/module/module_default/default.png', 'With CSS3, you can create rounded borders, add shadow to boxes, and use an image as a border - without using a design program, like Photoshop.\r\n\r\nIn this chapter you will learn about the following border properties:\r\n\r\nborder-radius\r\nbox-shadow\r\nborder-image', '<div>\r\n<h2 style=\\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 22px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal;\\">Browser Support</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\\">The numbers in the table specifies the first browser version that fully supports the property.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\\">Numbers followed by -webkit-, -moz-, or -o- specifies the first version that worked with a prefix.</p>\r\n\r\n<table class=\\"browserref notranslate\\" style=\\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; border-collapse: collapse; width: 821px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); line-height: normal;\\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th style=\\"font-size: 16px; height: 32px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); font-weight: normal; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); padding: 5px; vertical-align: middle; width: 113px; background-position: 50% 50%; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\\">Property</th>\r\n			<th class=\\"bsIE\\" style=\\"height: 32px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); font-weight: normal; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); padding: 5px; vertical-align: middle; background-image: url(http://www.w3schools.com/images/compatible_ie.gif); width: 113px; background-position: 50% 50%; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\\" title=\\"Internet Explorer\\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n			<th class=\\"bsChrome\\" style=\\"height: 32px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); font-weight: normal; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); padding: 5px; vertical-align: middle; background-image: url(http://www.w3schools.com/images/compatible_chrome.gif); width: 129px; background-position: 50% 50%; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\\" title=\\"Chrome\\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n			<th class=\\"bsFirefox\\" style=\\"height: 32px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); font-weight: normal; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); padding: 5px; vertical-align: middle; background-image: url(http://www.w3schools.com/images/compatible_firefox.gif); width: 136px; background-position: 50% 50%; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\\" title=\\"Firefox\\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n			<th class=\\"bsSafari\\" style=\\"height: 32px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); font-weight: normal; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); padding: 5px; vertical-align: middle; background-image: url(http://www.w3schools.com/images/compatible_safari.gif); width: 136px; background-position: 50% 50%; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\\" title=\\"Safari\\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n			<th class=\\"bsOpera\\" style=\\"height: 32px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); font-weight: normal; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); padding: 5px; vertical-align: middle; background-image: url(http://www.w3schools.com/images/compatible_opera.gif); width: 128px; background-position: 50% 50%; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\\" title=\\"Opera\\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\\"background-color: rgb(246, 244, 240);\\">\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">border-radius</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">9.0</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">5.0<br />\r\n			4.0 -webkit-</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">4.0<br />\r\n			3.0 -moz-</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">5.0<br />\r\n			3.1 -webkit-</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">10.5</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">box-shadow</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">9.0</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">10.0<br />\r\n			4.0 -webkit-</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">4.0<br />\r\n			3.5 -moz-</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">5.1<br />\r\n			3.1 -webkit-</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">10.5</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\\"background-color: rgb(246, 244, 240);\\">\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">border-image</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">11.0</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">16.0<br />\r\n			4.0 -webkit-</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">15.0<br />\r\n			3.5 -moz-</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">6.0<br />\r\n			3.1 -webkit-</td>\r\n			<td style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; border: 1px solid rgb(212, 212, 212); padding: 7px 5px; vertical-align: top;\\">15.0<br />\r\n			10.5 -o-</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr style=\\"background-color: rgb(212, 212, 212); color: rgb(212, 212, 212); height: 1px; border-top-width: 0px; clear: both; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal;\\" />\r\n<h2 style=\\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 22px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal;\\">CSS3 The border-radius Property - Rounded Corners</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\\">Adding rounded corners in CSS2 was tricky. We had to use different images for each corner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\\">In CSS3, creating rounded corners is easy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\\">In CSS3, the border-radius property is used to create rounded corners:</p>\r\n\r\n<div id=\\"rounded_borders\\" style=\\"background-image: url(http://www.w3schools.com/css/rounded_corners.gif); padding-top: 10px; width: 284px; height: 28px; text-align: center; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\\">This box has rounded corners!</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<div class=\\"example\\" style=\\"width: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(227, 227, 227); margin: 0px; padding: 10px; border-top-left-radius: 4px; border-top-right-radius: 4px; border-bottom-right-radius: 4px; border-bottom-left-radius: 4px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal;\\">\r\n<h2 class=\\"example\\" style=\\"font-size: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\\">Example</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px;\\">Add rounded corners to a div element:</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\\"example_code notranslate\\" style=\\"width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); padding: 4px 4px 4px 7px; border-left-width: 4px; border-left-style: solid; border-left-color: rgb(138, 192, 7); font-size: 14px; font-family: \\''courier new\\''; border-top-left-radius: 4px; border-top-right-radius: 4px; border-bottom-right-radius: 4px; border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\\">div<br />\r\n{<br />\r\nborder:2px solid;<br />\r\nborder-radius:25px;<br />\r\n}</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<a class=\\"tryitbtn\\" href=\\"http://www.w3schools.com/css/tryit.asp?filename=trycss3_border-radius\\" style=\\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-color: rgb(138, 192, 7); display: inline-block; font-weight: bold; font-size: 12px; text-align: center; padding: 3px 10px 4px; text-decoration: none; margin-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 5px; border: 1px solid rgb(138, 192, 7); border-top-left-radius: 5px; border-top-right-radius: 5px; border-bottom-right-radius: 5px; border-bottom-left-radius: 5px; white-space: nowrap;\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Try it yourself &raquo;</a></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr style=\\"background-color: rgb(212, 212, 212); color: rgb(212, 212, 212); height: 1px; border-top-width: 0px; clear: both; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal;\\" />\r\n<h2 style=\\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 22px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal;\\">CSS3 The box-shadow Property</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\\">In CSS3, the box-shadow property is used to add shadow to boxes:</p>\r\n\r\n<div id=\\"boxshadow\\" style=\\"background-image: url(http://www.w3schools.com/css/box_shadow.gif); width: 313px; height: 113px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;\\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<div class=\\"example\\" style=\\"width: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(227, 227, 227); margin: 0px; padding: 10px; border-top-left-radius: 4px; border-top-right-radius: 4px; border-bottom-right-radius: 4px; border-bottom-left-radius: 4px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal;\\">\r\n<h2 class=\\"example\\" style=\\"font-size: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\\">Example</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\\"line-height: 16.899999618530273px;\\">Add a box-shadow to a div element:</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\\"example_code notranslate\\" style=\\"width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); padding: 4px 4px 4px 7px; border-left-width: 4px; border-left-style: solid; border-left-color: rgb(138, 192, 7); font-size: 14px; font-family: \\''courier new\\''; border-top-left-radius: 4px; border-top-right-radius: 4px; border-bottom-right-radius: 4px; border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\\">div<br />\r\n{<br />\r\nbox-shadow: 10px 10px 5px #888888;<br />\r\n}</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<a class=\\"tryitbtn\\" href=\\"http://www.w3schools.com/css/tryit.asp?filename=trycss3_box-shadow\\" style=\\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-color: rgb(138, 192, 7); display: inline-block; font-weight: bold; font-size: 12px; text-align: center; padding: 3px 10px 4px; text-decoration: none; margin-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 5px; border: 1px solid rgb(138, 192, 7); border-top-left-radius: 5px; border-top-right-radius: